svg.desc:
#direction: right
[Control|Represents the base class for user interface (UI) elements that use a ControlTemplate to define their appearance.]
[ContentControl|Represents a control with a single piece of content of any type.]
[ButtonBase|Represents the base class for all Button controls.]
[Button|Represents a Windows button control, which reacts to the Click event.]
[RepeatButton|Represents a control that raises its Click event repeatedly from the time it is pressed until it is released.]
[TextBoxBase|An abstract base class that provides functionality for text editing controls, including TextBox and RichTextBox.]
[TextBox|Represents a control that can be used to display or edit unformatted text.]
[RichTextBox|Represents a rich editing control which operates on FlowDocument objects.]
[PasswordBox|Represents a control designed for entering and handling passwords.]
[DatePicker|Represents a control that allows the user to select a date.]
[Calendar|Represents a control that enables a user to select a date by using a visual calendar display.]
[RangeBase|Represents an element that has a value within a specific range.]
[Slider|Represents a control that lets the user select from a range of values by moving a Thumb control along a Track.]
[ToggleButton|Base class for controls that can switch states, such as CheckBox.]
[CheckBox|Represents a control that a user can select and clear.]
[RadioButton|Represents a button that can be selected, but not cleared, by a user. The IsChecked property of a RadioButton can be set by clicking it, but it can only be cleared programmatically.]
[FrameworkElement] <:- [Control] <:- [ContentControl]
[ContentControl] <:- [ButtonBase] <:- [Button] [ButtonBase] <:- [RepeatButton]
[Control] <:- [PasswordBox]
[Control] <:- [TextBoxBase]
[TextBoxBase] <- [TextBox]
[TextBoxBase] <- [RichTextBox]
[Control] <:- [DatePicker] [Control] <:- [Calendar]
[Control] <:- [RangeBase] <:-[Slider]
[ButtonBase] <:- [ToggleButton] <:- [CheckBox] [ToggleButton] <:- [RadioButton]
